                                                                <h2
                                                                    class="coh-heading ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-76563179-eeb5-42fa-b634-beb2bd110b2b coh-component-instance-76563179-eeb5-42fa-b634-beb2bd110b2b  dark-heading align-text-left coh-style-cfa-margin-bottom-lg     ssa-instance-8f7a7610536af1e1b8b7bd8abc9df389 coh-ce-cpt_heading-b45c50fc">
                                                                    Childhood Memories and Early Education</h2>
                                                                <div
                                                                    class="coh-wysiwyg ssa-component coh-component ssa-component-instance-ecd8d55f-acbe-49f1-b701-5ce030bcb7b6 coh-component-instance-ecd8d55f-acbe-49f1-b701-5ce030bcb7b6  coh-style-text-color-light-background       coh-style-cfa-margin-bottom-md coh-style-paragraph-100   ssa-instance-74594f6d693e12249b0d85cdbe8495d1 coh-ce-cpt_text-e4a5f5e1">
                                                                    <p><span dir="ltr">My early years were spent in
                                                                            Model Town, Lahore, where I attended Divisional
                                                                            Public School. I was a diligent student,
                                                                            especially excelling in languages, though
                                                                            mathematics was my Achilles' heel. Sports were
                                                                            my forte, and I was the school badminton
                                                                            champion and a proud Prefect.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            After completing my early education, I enrolled
                                                                            at Forman Christian College for F.Sc. However,
                                                                            my true academic turning point came at
                                                                            Government College, Lahore, where I initially
                                                                            pursued a Bachelor’s in Science. A bold decision
                                                                            to switch from science to commerce led me to
                                                                            leave Government College and embark on a new
                                                                            academic journey in business studies. This
                                                                            shift, guided by my father’s mentorship, became
                                                                            the foundation of my career.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            One memorable experience stands out: On my first
                                                                            day as a B.Com student, I was tested on journal
                                                                            entries, a topic I knew nothing about. I secured
                                                                            zero marks and faced public ridicule. That
                                                                            incident, rather than discouraging me, fueled my
                                                                            determination. By the end of my degree, I topped
                                                                            the Punjab University in Auditing and secured an
                                                                            overall third position at my college.
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            <br />
                                                                            This phase of my life taught me resilience. As
                                                                            the saying goes, <i
                                                                                style="white-space: nowrap;font-weight: 600;">"When
                                                                                the going
                                                                                gets tough, the
                                                                                tough get going." </i>
                                                                        </span></p>
